This paper is primarily focused on developing a query system for investigating complex attack behaviors in enterprise security. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses the domain-specific data model and storage, query language, and optimized query engine, which are related to database systems (cs.DB). The use of AI techniques for optimization suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) category. The paper also discusses the design and implementation of the query system, which is related to software engineering (cs.SE) and distributed computing (cs.DC).
